article.headline: Tennessee Tech 91, Jacksonville St. 74
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. -- Daniel Northern scored 22 points and went 10-for-10 from the free-throw line to lead Tennessee Tech to a 91-74 victory over Jacksonville State on Saturday, earning the eighth and final seed in the Ohio Valley Conference tournament. Tennessee Tech (12-17, 6-12) set a school record by shooting 96.7 percent form the free-throw line (29 of 30), surpassing a 95.7 percent effort (22 of 23) against Southern Mississippi during 1984-85. Jacksonville State (11-17, 5-13) cut the Golden Eagles' lead to 47-46 with 17:54 to play, but Tennessee Tech scored seven straight points to break the game open. Kevin Murphy scored 21 points and hit 6 of 6 free throws and Will Barnes added 12 points for the Golden Eagles. The Gamecocks were led by Nick Murphy with 18 points. Jeremy Bynum added 15, Stephen Hall tallied 14 and Brandon Crawford chipped in 12.
